  "text": "The Prometheus server repository enforces metric naming conventions across multiple components to ensure data consistency and correctness:\n\n1. **Metric Name Validation**: Files like `model/textparse/protobufparse.go` (line 451), `model/textparse/openmetricsparse.go` (line 513), and `model/textparse/promparse.go` (line 354) validate metric names against the configured validation scheme (UTF8 or Legacy) using `model.UTF8Validation.IsValidMetricName()` and validate help text as UTF-8 strings.\n\n2. **Label Name Validation**: Multiple files enforce label naming conventions:\n   - `model/labels/labels_common.go` (line 118): The `IsValid()` method validates both metric names and label names using `validationScheme.IsValidLabelName()`\n   - `model/relabel/relabel.go` (lines 140, 150, 159, 168): Validates target label names in relabel configurations\n   - `model/rulefmt/rulefmt.go` (lines 121, 247, 264, 278): Validates label names in recording and alert rules, and metric names for recording rules\n   - `prompb/io/prometheus/client/decoder.go` (line 245): Validates label names during protobuf metric decoding\n   - `promql/engine.go`, `promql/functions.go`, `promql/parser/printer.go`: Validate label names in PromQL operations\n   - `storage/remote/codec.go` (lines 854, 857): Validates metric and label names in remote write encoding\n   - `web/api/v1/api.go` (line 843): Validates label names in API requests\n\n3. **Unit Suffix Enforcement**: `model/textparse/openmetricsparse.go` (line 525-526) validates that unit suffixes are properly appended to metric names with underscore separation, ensuring metrics like `http_requests_total` correctly have `_total` as a unit suffix.\n\n4. **Help Text Validation**: All text parsers (`protobufparse.go`, `openmetricsparse.go`, `promparse.go`) validate help text is valid UTF-8, with `openmetricsparse.go` line 512-513 explicitly checking this.\n\n5. **Configuration Management**: `config/config.go` (line 509, 628, 635) manages the global metric name validation scheme configuration, allowing operators to choose between UTF-8 and legacy validation modes.\n\nThese validations collectively enforce the Prometheus metric naming convention that requires metric names to follow snake_case format with appropriate unit suffixes, have valid label names, and include non-empty help text for proper metric documentation."
}

